pull.title: [Util] Update tinyformat.h
pull.body:
Updates `tinyformat.h` to commit c42f/tinyformat@689695c upstream. Including:
https://github.com/c42f/tinyformat/commit/8a2812d8480bfb66923eea0bb5cdda79fe4f17ba
https://github.com/c42f/tinyformat/commit/5d9e05a3479d1b2ec6a4602fd797f0ec26440db2
https://github.com/c42f/tinyformat/commit/48e2e48789907f80a7aec24a3f1d69196b78ed43

@achow101 mentioned that since upgrading to Ubuntu 17.10 (GCC 7), tinyformat had been throwing lots of -Wimplicit-fallthrough warnings. However fallthrough warnings should have been silenced by #10489. cc @theuni.

The upstream commit to fix fallthrough warnings is in this PR https://github.com/c42f/tinyformat/pull/39.

The last time tinyformat.h was updated in this repo was in #8274.

events.body: This does indeed silence the `-Wimplicit-fallthrough` warnings

issue.title: Build: quiet annoying warnings
issue.body:
Merging a pair of bitcoin PRs to silence annoying warnings.
In particular, gcc7 `cc1plus: warning: unrecognized command line option "-Wno-self-assign" `

Merging https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/7954 undoes the previous PR https://github.com/dashpay/dash/pull/1622 silencing implicit-fallthrough warnings.
This then allows proper merge of https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/10489.

Of course, it would be better to fix the source of the warnings but most are in dependencies.
Note: the tinyformat library is the cause of most implicit-fallthrough warnings -
these are fixed in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/11573

issue.title: tinyformat.h upstream changes
issue.body:
`src/tinyformat.h` is an external project (https://github.com/c42f/tinyformat).
This PR will take care of syncing the file importing all changes made in the
upstream project. 

This will import a series of Core PRs, namely:
- #8274  
- #9417
- #9963
- #10969 (partially applied)
- #11573

(***This patch depends on #902***)

#9963 is particularly useful because:
```
"Instead of having an exception propagate into the program 
(which at worst causes a crash) when an error happens while 
formatting a log message, just print a message to the log. 
This message clearly indicates what log message was formatted 
wrongly, and what error happened during formatting it."
```

This means that rather than having annoying message on `stdout`, that e.g. could lead to false test failure, like this one:

```
************************                                                                                                                                                                          
EXCEPTION: St13runtime_error                                                                                                                                                                      
tinyformat: Too many conversion specifiers in format string                                                                                                                                       
bitcoin in ProcessMessages()                                                                                                                                                                      
 ```
an error message in the log will be printed, e.g:

```
  2018-01-11 17:31:48 Error "tinyformat: Too many conversion specifiers in format string" while formatting log message: receive version message: %s: version %d, blocks=%d, us=%s, peer=%d%s %s```

comments.body: Should this be `NULL` or `nullptr`? IIRC we prefer to use `nullptr` instead of `NULL` and tinyformat is something that we have made our own changes to before.

In https://github.com/c42f/tinyformat/pull/43 it was originally `nullptr`, then changed to `NULL`. However if `nullptr` is preferred we'll use that, as we are already maintaining our own changes to this code.
In the [Developer Notes](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/developer-notes.md) is written "nullptr is preferred over NULL or (void*)0."
